The paper discusses the use of generative adversarial nets (GANs) and variational auto-encoders for distribution modeling, dataset augmentation, image-to-image translation, and feature learning. These topics are commonly studied in the machine learning subfields of computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the sample complexity of distance metrics, which is a topic commonly studied in the subfield of information theory (cs.IT). However, the primary focus of the paper is on improving GAN training, which is a topic commonly studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.IT.
